<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="broken-adj">broken <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'brəʊkən/    美 /'broʊkən/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>破碎的；损坏的；折断的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a broken heart</strong> 
破碎的心</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The glass is broken.
玻璃(杯)碎了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The copy machine is broken again. 
复印机又出毛病了。</p><footer> 2008 上海</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His leg was broken. 
他的腿断了。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(关系) 破裂的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>broken marriage / home</strong> 
破裂的婚姻/家庭</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>断断续续的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>broken time 
零星时间</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>遭违背的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a broken promise 
背弃的诺言</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>不流利的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>broken English</strong> 
蹩脚的英语</p></div></div>